1	#!/usr/bin/env node
2	'use strict';
3	// eval/calibration-known-bad/run.js - the earn-your-zero gate.
4	//
5	// Every analyser/gate in tools/ must FAIL on seeded known-bad input each run: a checker
6	// that reports zero findings on its own calibration fixture is broken, and its green
7	// tick on real code is worthless (the confident-zero disease). This runner invokes each
8	// relevant checker in --calibrate mode and FAILS (exit 1) if any checker reports zero
9	// findings on its fixture.
10	//
11	// THE --calibrate CONTRACT (coordinate with the tools/ agent; documented in README.md):
12	//   node tools/<checker> --calibrate
13	//   - the checker scans eval/calibration-known-bad/fixtures/ (this directory) only
14	//   - prints a single JSON object to stdout: {"checker":"<name>","findings":[{"file":"...","line":N,"rule":"...","message":"..."}]}
15	//   - exits 0 whether or not findings exist (--calibrate reports; this runner judges)
16	//
17	// Checker discovery: each entry lists candidate paths under tools/. While the tools/
18	// agent is still building (P0 runs in parallel), a missing checker is reported as
19	// SKIPPED with a warning and does not fail the run - pass --strict to make missing
20	// checkers fail (CI flips to --strict the moment tools/ lands).
21	//
22	// The payload-contract check needs no external tool: it runs payload/contract
23	// validatePayload() directly, so at least one earn-your-zero gate is live from commit 1.
24	//
25	// Usage: node eval/calibration-known-bad/run.js [--strict] [--json]
26	// Exit codes: 0 = every present checker caught its fixture; 1 = a checker reported zero
27	// findings on its fixture (or --strict and a checker is missing); 2 = runner error.
28	
